cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper deals with deep learning models operating on 3D data, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as the paper focuses on understanding the spatial arrangement of objects and evaluating the performance of state-of-the-art models. The second likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper deals with deep learning models and their robustness. The third likely category is cs.RO (Robotics), as the paper mentions autonomous navigation, which is a common application of robotics. The fourth likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper deals with neural networks and their performance in an adversarial setting. The fifth likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as the paper evaluates the vulnerability of deep learning models to occlusion attacks.
